],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705182,"age":1,"year":"1066","julianDay":2110409,"title":"Battle of Hastings","description":"Battle of Hastings was fought between the Norman-French army and the battle-wary English army on October 14, 1066. Duke William of Normandy believed he was the rightful king rather than Harold, who had been crowned king several months earlier. Harold was killed in battle and William was crowned king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705183,"age":21,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705184,"age":31,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Euphemia de Balliol was born in 1065, in Holderness, Yorkshire, England as the daughter of Ameline De Montgomery. She married Malcolm mac Malcolm, Earl of Ross in 1086, in Holderness, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died about 1100, in Cromarty, Cromartyshire, Scotland, at the age of 36."},"et":{"1065–about 1100":"1065–umbes 1100","1065–1100":"1065–1100","1064–1098":"1064–1098","1090–1119":"1090–1119","1035–1084":"1035–1084","1090":"1090","1066":"1066","1065":"1065","1098":"1098","1086